dc_description_s: The greater part of the translation into English is by Laurin Zilliacus. cf. Preface of atlas. ""Atlas of Finland 1925 is issued as a single edition with explanatory headings in both of the languages of the country, Finnish and Swedish, and in English. The text is issued separately in each of the three languages: the English text constitutes volume 48 of Fennia"". Atlas of Finland 1925. Text, p. [ii] The atlas here catalogued has title in the three languages: Suomen kartasto. Atlas of Finland. Atlas över Finland 1925. (At head of title: Suomen maantleteellinen seura. The Geographical society of Finland. Geografiska sällskapet i Finland) Imprint date on verso of t.-p.: 1925-28. The earlier atlases of Finland, 1899 and 1910, were issued by the Sällskapet för Finlands geografi, and are catalogued under that heading. Later edition published under title: Suomen kartasto.
